TEMBA Bavuma will be in line for major awards at the annual Cricket SA Awards next Monday. The Proteas batsman and skipper has been nominated for the Test Cricketer of the Year and SA Men’s Cricketer of the Year awards. However, he will face still competition from Proteas fast bowler Anrich Nortje, who has been nominated in a whopping six in different categories, including men’s Cricketer of the Year award.      LEADING MEN’S NOMINATIONS: Anrich Nortje: One-Day International Cricketer of the Year, Test Cricketer of the Year, KFC Streetwise Award, CSA Delivery of the Year, SA Fans’ Player of the Year and SA Men’s Cricketer of the Year. Aiden Markram: T20 International Cricketer of the Year, Test Cricketer of the Year, KFC Streetwise Award and SA Men’s Cricketer of the Year. Temba Bavuma: Test Cricketer of the Year and SA Men’s Cricketer of the Year. Rassie van der Dussen: T20 International Cricketer of the Year, One-Day International Cricketer of the Year and SA Men’s Cricketer of the Year. In addition, the jury is still out on the SA Men’s Players’ Player of the Year.  LEADING WOMEN’S NOMINATIONS:        